#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Custom pomodoro timer with i3blocks integration.

Subcommands:
  toggle      Start, pause, or resume the timer.
  stop        Cancel the current pomodoro entirely.
  skip        Skip the current phase and advance to the next.
  reset       Restart the current phase from the beginning.
  status      Print human-readable status.
  status --json
  status --i3blocks   Three-line output for i3blocks.
  analyze [--today|--week|--all]   Summarize the log.
  review [--json] [--start D] [--end D]
                                   Week-in-review: commits, completed tasks,
                                   learnings, and focus pomodoros for a week.
                                   Defaults to the last completed Sun-Sat week.
  notifications [--since-id N]     Show muted notification backlog in rofi.
  pause-reason [--duration N]      Prompt for a reason for the last pause; logged.
  tasks list [--include-completed] [--tag NAME]
  tasks add                        Read JSON body from stdin: {title, due_at?, scheduled_at?, long_term?, notes?}
                                   #tags in the title are parsed out and stored as tags.
  tasks update <id>                Read JSON body from stdin with fields to merge (null clears).
  tasks complete <id>
  tasks uncomplete <id>
  tasks delete <id>
  set-task                         Read JSON body from stdin: {task_id} | {task_text} | {clear: true}
  learning add                     Read JSON body from stdin: {text}. Append today's learning.
  learning list [--today]
  learning today                   JSON: {date, count, logged, prompt_hour, entries}.
  learning nudge                   Notify if nothing learned today (for the evening timer).
  learning recall                  JSON: one past learning (from a previous week) to resurface today, or {}.
  motd add <url>                   Register a source document URL.
  motd sources                     List registered sources.
  motd remove <id>                 Drop a source and its snippets.
  motd build [--source ID] [--force]   Fetch sources and extract key passages via Claude.
  motd current [--json]            Print today's message of the day.

Config:  ~/.config/pomodoro/config.json (auto-created with defaults)
State:   ~/.local/state/pomodoro/state.json
Tasks:   ~/.local/state/pomodoro/tasks.json
Log:     ~/.local/state/pomodoro/log.jsonl
Learnings: ~/.local/state/pomodoro/learnings.jsonl
MOTD:    ~/.local/state/pomodoro/motd_sources.json, motd_snippets.json

`motd build` calls an OpenRouter (OpenAI-compatible) model and needs
OPENROUTER_API_KEY (read from the environment or a repo-local .env); nothing
else does. No third-party packages — stdlib only. Model and endpoint are
configurable via `motd_model` / `motd_base_url` in config.
"""

